nor' states, in an examination of this crucial period for the left in Europe from a number of perspectives. Comparisons are presented between the various EU member states, as well as different party families of the left, from social democracy through green left to radical left.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGlobal Financial Crisis, 2008-2009xPolitical aspectszEurope. 0aSocialismzEurope. 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  aEuropean green left.  aEuropean integration.  aEuropean left.  aEuropean radical left.  aEuropean social democracy.  aPodemos.  aSYRIZA.  afinancial collapse.  afinancial crash.1 aBruge, Ilvija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBukovskis, Karlis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmes, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKatsourides, Yiannos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNavarro, Julien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNikolakakis, Nikolaos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaunio, Tapio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRico Motos, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoder, Knut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoder, Knut, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSeddone, Antonella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStorey, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aToriz Ramos, Cláudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary